HEADWORD: Proser
<hw>Pros"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A writer
of prose.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who talks or writes tediously.</def> <rj><au>Sir
